1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:05,296
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:12,387
‪[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,185
[guard] <i>Because someone tried</i>
<i>to escape from you,</i>

4
00:00:19,769 --> 00:00:21,187
<i>all of you get no dinner!</i>

5
00:00:21,271 --> 00:00:25,108
Now, we’re all not going to eat
because of this idiot!

6
00:00:25,191 --> 00:00:26,192
[Red] <i>I want him banned here!</i>

7
00:00:26,276 --> 00:00:27,736
[thugs grunting]

8
00:00:27,819 --> 00:00:29,779
[Lorna] <i>He won’t be able to come</i>
<i>back here ever again.</i>

9
00:00:29,863 --> 00:00:35,243
Why don’t we all work together, so we can
escape and report them to the police?

10
00:00:35,326 --> 00:00:38,246
[Darryl] <i>The syndicate that holds</i>
<i>us here has deep connections, Ame.</i>

11
00:00:38,329 --> 00:00:40,290
[Ibyang] <i>Did you find her?</i>

12
00:00:40,373 --> 00:00:41,958
Why isn’t she with you?

13
00:00:42,041 --> 00:00:44,711
I’ll handle it. Don’t meddle, okay?

14
00:00:44,794 --> 00:00:47,630
You know, you look like Catriona Gray.

15
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:48,590
PREVIOUSLY

16
00:00:48,673 --> 00:00:51,217
[Tonet] <i>Do you want to be</i>
<i>Little Miss Catriona Gray?</i>

17
00:00:51,301 --> 00:00:53,219
Philippines!

18
00:00:53,303 --> 00:00:54,137
[Tonet] Very good!

19
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:56,306
Son of a thread!

20
00:00:56,389 --> 00:01:01,144
I’m the newest and most beautiful
shop assistant you have!

21
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:03,521
So, who accepted you? Who interviewed you?

22
00:01:04,105 --> 00:01:05,148
Miss Cita!

23
00:01:05,231 --> 00:01:07,984
- Did you pass her interview?
- I passed with flying colors.

24
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:08,985
Well, with me, you didn’t.

25
00:01:09,069 --> 00:01:10,070
Huh?

26
00:01:10,153 --> 00:01:11,488
You failed.

27
00:01:11,571 --> 00:01:14,157
[Atoy] I need a disguise
to get inside Endless Nights.

28
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:18,369
I saw Tonet had talent in makeup.

29
00:01:18,453 --> 00:01:19,412
Maybe she can help you.

30
00:01:19,996 --> 00:01:20,997
That’s right.

31
00:01:21,081 --> 00:01:23,249
But you fired her, remember?

32
00:01:23,792 --> 00:01:25,335
[chuckles]

33
00:01:25,418 --> 00:01:26,753
You we're supposed to be 'da one,
but it turns out you're very mean!

34
00:01:26,836 --> 00:01:28,421
Acting as if you have
the world on your shoulders.

35
00:01:28,505 --> 00:01:32,175
[funky music playing]

36
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:34,052
- Tonet.
- [shouts] What?!

37
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:36,513
What?

38
00:01:36,596 --> 00:01:39,224
Atoy? This is unexpected.

39
00:01:39,307 --> 00:01:40,600
Sorry, you surprised me.

40
00:01:40,683 --> 00:01:43,186
No, actually…

41
00:01:45,021 --> 00:01:46,397
I changed my mind.

42
00:01:47,065 --> 00:01:48,399
[gentle music playing]

43
00:01:48,483 --> 00:01:49,484
Come in.

44
00:01:50,401 --> 00:01:51,402
Huh?

45
00:01:51,486 --> 00:01:55,740
Ah, I mean, you’re accepted.

46
00:01:56,449 --> 00:01:58,743
You can now be an assistant
in my sewing shop.

47
00:01:58,827 --> 00:02:00,203
[giggles, squeals softly]

48
00:02:02,038 --> 00:02:05,166
Eh… Sorry about earlier.

49
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:07,669
I was a little hotheaded earlier.

50
00:02:08,753 --> 00:02:09,921
That was just a little?

51
00:02:10,004 --> 00:02:10,922
[funky music playing]

52
00:02:11,005 --> 00:02:12,048
Wow.

53
00:02:12,590 --> 00:02:13,967
You were really grumpy.

54
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:15,635
Okay.

55
00:02:16,553 --> 00:02:17,804
Say please first.

56
00:02:23,268 --> 00:02:24,477
[in English] Please?

57
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:28,606
Come on. I need your help.

58
00:02:31,401 --> 00:02:32,610
Fine.

59
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:36,781
You know, you hurt my feelings earlier!

60
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:41,077
And also, don’t be like that.

61
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:43,663
What if your hair recedes?

62
00:02:43,746 --> 00:02:44,956
That’s on you too.

63
00:02:45,623 --> 00:02:47,876
And you’re trying to persuade me,
but you didn’t even bring flowers.

64
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:48,960
Is that proper?

65
00:02:49,043 --> 00:02:51,087
Oh, you have too much to say.

66
00:02:51,170 --> 00:02:52,255
I already said please.

67
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:55,091
Me, I rarely ask.
If you don’t want to, then don’t…

68
00:02:55,174 --> 00:02:56,759
Oh, just kidding! [chuckles]

69
00:02:56,843 --> 00:02:57,927
That was just a joke!

70
00:02:58,011 --> 00:02:59,846
I just took advantage of the moment!

71
00:02:59,929 --> 00:03:00,972
You’re OA!

72
00:03:01,055 --> 00:03:02,849
It just feels so good. Sorry.

73
00:03:02,932 --> 00:03:07,353
Here, okay, I agree.
What do you want? What… What do you need?

74
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:08,563
We’re good?

75
00:03:08,646 --> 00:03:10,356
- You’ll help me?
- Yes, okay.

76
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,524
It's just that…

77
00:03:11,608 --> 00:03:13,026
I have a gig on Saturday.

78
00:03:13,109 --> 00:03:14,319
I need help.

79
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:16,946
Do my makeup.

80
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:19,115
- [snips]
- [sewing machine whirring]

81
00:03:19,198 --> 00:03:22,076
[in Visayan] What kind of a gig is this?
Do I need to give you a perm?

82
00:03:22,952 --> 00:03:24,287
[in Visayan] I just have an audition.

83
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:26,915
Oh my gosh! You're also Bisaya?

84
00:03:28,124 --> 00:03:31,753
Oh my gosh! We’re really meant to be.
I knew it. We’re really meant to be.

85
00:03:34,255 --> 00:03:38,635
[upbeat playing music]

86
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:06,913
[mischievous music playing]

87
00:04:06,996 --> 00:04:09,666
Sir! Just by the side, please!

88
00:04:28,226 --> 00:04:29,477
[brooding music playing]

89
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:32,272
I’m still thinking how
I can re-enter Endless Nights,

90
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:33,815
since I’m wanted there.

91
00:04:34,524 --> 00:04:37,568
So, for now, I’ll probably just do
what I was really tasked to do.

92
00:04:37,652 --> 00:04:39,779
I’ll look for Mercardo’s rooster.

93
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:43,408
[Ibyang] <i>Looks like no one</i>
<i>will save you, Big Sister Ame.</i>

94
00:04:43,908 --> 00:04:45,618
<i>So, it’s up to me!</i>

95
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:50,873
[curious music playing]

96
00:04:55,169 --> 00:04:57,171
Hey, hurry up. We still
have a lot to carry here.

97
00:04:57,255 --> 00:04:58,798
[man] Okay, bro, just a moment.

98
00:05:00,842 --> 00:05:01,926
Let me pee first.

99
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:31,122
[stirring music playing]

100
00:06:24,008 --> 00:06:25,802
Come on. Let’s carry this water spinach.

101
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:26,803
Hurry up!

102
00:06:28,888 --> 00:06:31,015
[man groans]

103
00:06:32,141 --> 00:06:33,184
This is so heavy!

104
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:35,186
Are you sure this is just
water spinach inside?

105
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:37,480
Go ahead. Check if you want.

106
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:41,859
[tense music playing]

107
00:06:41,943 --> 00:06:43,736
Okay, okay, let’s finish this.

108
00:06:52,036 --> 00:06:53,037
[grunts]

109
00:06:53,955 --> 00:06:54,789
[man grunts]

110
00:06:54,872 --> 00:06:55,873
Okay, push.

111
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:59,794
[upbeat music playing]

112
00:06:59,877 --> 00:07:02,922
[man grunts]

113
00:07:09,387 --> 00:07:10,721
Ma’am, the deliveries have arrived.

114
00:07:10,805 --> 00:07:11,973
Please sign here.

115
00:07:13,474 --> 00:07:15,184
Okay, bring those inside.

116
00:07:16,352 --> 00:07:18,813
[upbeat music continues]

117
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:21,816
[Lorna] You.

118
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:24,735
Where are our additional janitors?

119
00:07:24,819 --> 00:07:26,112
They’re not here yet, Ma’am Lorna.

120
00:07:26,195 --> 00:07:28,322
But the agency already called.
They said they’re on the way.

121
00:07:30,616 --> 00:07:32,118
[phone ringing]

122
00:07:32,201 --> 00:07:33,411
Hey.

123
00:07:33,494 --> 00:07:34,662
Hey, bro, how are you?

124
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:37,915
Wow, that’s a good gig.

125
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:41,002
But I can’t anymore now.

126
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:45,965
I already got a job as a janitor.

127
00:07:46,048 --> 00:07:47,341
Bossing, thank you!

128
00:07:47,425 --> 00:07:48,301
Thank you, Boss.

129
00:07:49,051 --> 00:07:50,595
It’s perfect. Today’s my first day.

130
00:07:51,262 --> 00:07:56,476
[thrilling music playing]

131
00:07:59,020 --> 00:07:59,979
Hmm?

132
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:02,023
Where’s my uniform?

133
00:08:03,316 --> 00:08:04,650
Even my ID is gone!

134
00:08:05,276 --> 00:08:06,819
Oh, no! Where could it be?

135
00:08:08,738 --> 00:08:10,907
[thrilling music continues]

136
00:08:28,132 --> 00:08:29,675
I’ll take this out first.

137
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:30,760
Okay.

138
00:08:31,344 --> 00:08:34,931
[curious music playing]

139
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:38,476
[sighs]

140
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:48,444
[curious music continues]

141
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:49,946
I'M AT WORK, YOU SEE?
DON'T BE JEALOUS, BABE…

142
00:08:50,029 --> 00:08:52,031
They know that I’m at work.

143
00:09:14,303 --> 00:09:18,266
As they say, no big thing escapes notice.

144
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:23,271
[breathing heavily]

145
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:25,606
Don’t worry anymore, Big Sister Ame.

146
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:26,816
I’m on my way!

147
00:09:26,899 --> 00:09:30,319
[breathing heavily]

148
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:38,536
Efren Santos?

149
00:09:38,619 --> 00:09:39,787
Here, Boss.

150
00:09:39,870 --> 00:09:42,373
- Alwyn Reyes?
- Present!

151
00:09:42,456 --> 00:09:43,583
Jeffrey Matulak?

152
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:47,837
Jeffrey Matulak?

153
00:09:48,963 --> 00:09:50,006
Boss.

154
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:52,341
[rousing music playing]

155
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:53,509
Present, ma’am.

156
00:10:01,892 --> 00:10:05,730
[exciting music playing]

157
00:10:10,151 --> 00:10:11,360
Hey, Karla!

158
00:10:11,444 --> 00:10:13,237
We’ll use the court now.

159
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:15,239
I’ve got my friends with me.

160
00:10:15,323 --> 00:10:16,324
Nice.

161
00:10:16,407 --> 00:10:17,450
Did you pay?

162
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:20,036
Sorry, miss, but you’ve been here
for a while already.

163
00:10:21,245 --> 00:10:23,414
We came around a while ago
and we let you guys play.

164
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:24,373
It’s our turn, right?

165
00:10:24,457 --> 00:10:26,334
- [boys] Oh, no!
- [boy] English!

166
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:28,252
This is gonna be hard.

167
00:10:28,836 --> 00:10:31,130
[in English] Hey, you!

168
00:10:31,839 --> 00:10:32,673
[in English] Yes!

169
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:34,467
- All right!
- [boys] Yes!

170
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:35,843
- [boy] Nice one!
- [Karla] Me, me, me.

171
00:10:35,926 --> 00:10:37,428
- [Karla] Here, here.
- [boy] Okay, fine.

172
00:10:37,511 --> 00:10:39,013
[in English] This is
by first come first serve.

173
00:10:39,096 --> 00:10:40,056
[boy] What?

174
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:41,849
[in English] We’re not finished playing
unless we finish you.

175
00:10:41,932 --> 00:10:43,184
- [boy 1] Whoa!
- [boy 2] What?

176
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:44,477
- [boy 1] English!
- English too!

177
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:46,020
You’re so good!

178
00:10:46,103 --> 00:10:47,396
Oh, okay, okay… This is what we'll do.

179
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,774
Let's make a bet! Three on three.

180
00:10:50,399 --> 00:10:51,984
- Game?
- How much?

181
00:10:52,068 --> 00:10:53,235
[boy laughs]

182
00:10:54,695 --> 00:10:55,696
- [boy 1] Game?
- [boy 2] Hey, Karla.

183
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:57,740
- [Karla] Yes?
- Guys, do your best!

184
00:10:57,823 --> 00:10:59,283
We’re playing for ice water!
We don’t have money to pay them.

185
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:00,534
Don't be scared, Billy.

186
00:11:01,243 --> 00:11:03,954
- We won't lose to these outsiders!
- [girl] That's right.

187
00:11:04,789 --> 00:11:06,540
- Let's go!
- That's right!

188
00:11:06,624 --> 00:11:07,958
- Nice!
- [girl] Game!

189
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:09,835
- All right, game! Ball up top.
- [girl] Game!

190
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:12,004
Be careful.

191
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:20,679
Karla! Where's the kid you were with?

192
00:11:21,347 --> 00:11:24,308
She's fine! She just bought some food.

193
00:11:24,392 --> 00:11:25,726
- [girl] Food?
- Yes.

194
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:27,061
[whimsical music playing]

195
00:11:27,144 --> 00:11:28,354
[girl] Let's go!

196
00:11:29,063 --> 00:11:30,106
[indistinct speech]

197
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:34,527
[sinister music playing]

198
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:38,989
[in English] Okay.

199
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:40,491
Okay, this is all complete, right?

200
00:11:41,992 --> 00:11:44,995
Now, listen to me carefully.

201
00:11:45,579 --> 00:11:48,624
There's a lot to clean at the back area.

202
00:11:48,707 --> 00:11:51,460
I want it thoroughly cleaned.

203
00:11:51,544 --> 00:11:52,461
Okay?

204
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:56,841
So do a good job
if you don't want any problems.

205
00:11:57,425 --> 00:11:59,635
- Understood?
- [janitors, in English] Yes, ma'am.

206
00:11:59,718 --> 00:12:01,011
Do you understand what I'm saying?

207
00:12:01,095 --> 00:12:02,388
[in unison, in Engish] Yes, ma'am.

208
00:12:02,471 --> 00:12:03,764
That's the answer I was looking for!

209
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:05,224
Okay, follow me.

210
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:19,196
[whimsical music playing]

211
00:12:59,987 --> 00:13:00,863
Uh…

212
00:13:01,572 --> 00:13:04,033
‪[muttering]

213
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:04,950
‪[beeping]

214
00:13:09,914 --> 00:13:10,998
[warped beep]

215
00:13:11,081 --> 00:13:13,042
[sighs] What's this?

216
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:15,169
Why does it have to be numbers?

217
00:13:15,252 --> 00:13:17,004
I don't even like math!

218
00:13:17,588 --> 00:13:18,422
‪[sighs]

219
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:19,715
‪[beeping]

220
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:24,762
[warped beep]

221
00:13:26,013 --> 00:13:27,640
Don't quit, Ibyang!

222
00:13:27,723 --> 00:13:30,768
This is no different than the lottery.

223
00:13:30,851 --> 00:13:32,728
[deep breath]

224
00:13:33,229 --> 00:13:37,650
[tense music playing]

225
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:41,779
What’s the score? Ten all, right?

226
00:13:41,862 --> 00:13:42,738
Yes!

227
00:13:42,821 --> 00:13:45,324
Guys, do your best!

228
00:13:45,407 --> 00:13:46,909
We’re playing for ice water!

229
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:49,620
Guys, we gotta play well.
We don’t have money to pay them.

230
00:13:49,703 --> 00:13:51,956
[tense music playing]

231
00:13:52,039 --> 00:13:54,083
[in English] We can’t lose
this game, Gavin.

232
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:55,334
[in English] Don’t worry, Jason.

233
00:13:55,834 --> 00:13:56,877
I’ll guard the girl.

234
00:13:57,962 --> 00:14:00,422
[thrilling music playing]

235
00:14:12,851 --> 00:14:14,853
- Up to 12 only, right?
- Yes, all the way!

236
00:14:14,937 --> 00:14:15,771
- Game!
- [boy] Game!

237
00:14:17,064 --> 00:14:18,941
- [boy 1] Gavin, Gavin!
- [boy 2] Mine, mine, mine.

238
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:21,360
- [in English] To your left, to your left!
- [boy, in English] Left, left!

239
00:14:21,443 --> 00:14:24,613
[indistinct chattering]

240
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:27,116
- Putoy is open!
- [boy] Go!

241
00:14:27,199 --> 00:14:28,409
Shoot it now!

242
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,078
[boys cheering]

243
00:14:31,161 --> 00:14:32,997
[in English] Let’s go!

244
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,331
[Karla] Whoo!

245
00:14:34,415 --> 00:14:36,333
Hey! You’re so good!

246
00:14:36,417 --> 00:14:38,752
- [cheering]
- [boy] Whoo! Let’s go! Let’s go!

247
00:14:38,836 --> 00:14:41,213
- [cheering]
- [Karla] There it is! Let’s go!

248
00:14:41,297 --> 00:14:43,757
Oh! Oh, pay up.

249
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:44,925
[in English] How about a rematch?

250
00:14:45,009 --> 00:14:48,512
[in English] Yes, last game.
Winner takes all.

251
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:49,555
Karla, don’t say yes.

252
00:14:49,638 --> 00:14:51,599
- We might lose.
- Correct.

253
00:14:51,682 --> 00:14:53,434
- Yes.
- Game!

254
00:14:54,602 --> 00:14:57,313
I’ll shoot a three pointer. If I miss,

255
00:14:57,396 --> 00:14:59,231
- I’ll pay the wager.
- [boy shrieks]

256
00:14:59,857 --> 00:15:01,233
[in English] Sounds like a good deal.

257
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:04,612
No, no, no. Three pointers are too easy.

258
00:15:05,112 --> 00:15:06,363
[in English] Halfcourt shot.

259
00:15:06,447 --> 00:15:07,531
- What?
- [girl] Oh!

260
00:15:07,615 --> 00:15:10,200
Looks like Pretty Boy
seems he is challenging you!

261
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:11,994
- Okay!
- [Karla scoffs]

262
00:15:12,494 --> 00:15:14,997
Karla, we’re not that lucky. Let’s go!

263
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:16,957
[thrilling music continues]

264
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:17,917
Game?

265
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:19,793
Okay, game.

266
00:15:19,877 --> 00:15:21,837
- [in English] Okay!
- [Karla in English] Watch and learn, boys!

267
00:15:23,797 --> 00:15:25,007
- [girl] You can do it, Karla!
- [boy] Let’s go, Karla!

268
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:26,550
- [boy] You can do it!
- [girl] Whoo!

269
00:15:26,634 --> 00:15:27,676
Is this okay?

270
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,053
- [boy 1] Okay.
- [boy 2] Go, that’s fine!

271
00:15:29,136 --> 00:15:30,054
- This is solid.
- [boy] Game!

272
00:15:30,137 --> 00:15:31,138
Oh!

273
00:15:35,726 --> 00:15:36,810
- [upbeat music playing]
- [Karla laughs]

274
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:39,813
[team cheering]

275
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:42,399
- [boy] Let’s go, Karla!
- [indistinct chattering]

276
00:15:42,483 --> 00:15:45,653
- [Karla] Let’s go, guys!
- [whooping]

277
00:15:45,736 --> 00:15:47,321
[upbeat music playing]

278
00:15:47,404 --> 00:15:49,365
Ey, ey, ey, ey!

279
00:15:49,448 --> 00:15:50,741
[indistinct chattering]

280
00:15:50,824 --> 00:15:53,118
[whooping]

281
00:15:54,411 --> 00:15:55,704
- [Ibyang muffled screams]
- [Atoy shushes]

282
00:15:55,788 --> 00:15:57,414
- [Ibyang muffled speech]
- [Atoy] One wrong press there,

283
00:15:57,498 --> 00:15:59,166
the alarm will go off!

284
00:15:59,249 --> 00:16:02,252
[muffled grunting]

285
00:16:02,336 --> 00:16:04,296
[shushes]

286
00:16:04,380 --> 00:16:05,339
[whispers] Keep quiet.

287
00:16:06,799 --> 00:16:09,134
- Master Grumpy?
- [whispers] Yes, don’t make any noise.

288
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:10,719
- Is that you?
- [whispers] Yes.

289
00:16:11,303 --> 00:16:12,554
Why is your hair different?

290
00:16:12,638 --> 00:16:13,847
Ah, just keep your mouth shut.

291
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:15,891
[Lorna] What’s happening?

292
00:16:16,392 --> 00:16:18,352
Why is there a child here?

293
00:16:18,894 --> 00:16:20,479
I know him!

294
00:16:20,562 --> 00:16:22,356
You know this kid?

295
00:16:22,439 --> 00:16:25,901
[suspenseful music playing]

296
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:27,277
[Atoy] Uh…

297
00:16:34,702 --> 00:16:37,037
[melancholic music playing]

298
00:16:47,548 --> 00:16:48,632
[soft sobbing]

299
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:53,303
Ame.

300
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:55,347
Stop it.

301
00:16:58,892 --> 00:17:00,269
I’m sorry.

302
00:17:01,061 --> 00:17:04,064
I’m just thinking about Ibyang,

303
00:17:04,148 --> 00:17:05,899
the girl who was with me.

304
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:07,067
[sobs]

305
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:09,194
She’s still so small.

306
00:17:10,070 --> 00:17:11,822
Is someone taking care of her?

307
00:17:11,905 --> 00:17:14,033
[sobbing]

308
00:17:14,616 --> 00:17:16,952
Yes, it is what it is.

309
00:17:17,453 --> 00:17:19,830
But you can’t keep crying like that.

310
00:17:20,497 --> 00:17:23,751
You think that will help
you see her again?

311
00:17:26,295 --> 00:17:28,047
Then what should I do?

312
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:29,214
Be strong.

313
00:17:29,798 --> 00:17:31,633
You must always win,

314
00:17:31,717 --> 00:17:34,261
because that’s the only way
to get out of here.

315
00:17:37,181 --> 00:17:40,142
Even that man you said you saw?

316
00:17:40,225 --> 00:17:43,645
With all the guards here, he’s useless!

317
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:50,235
No one else can help you
get out of here but yourself.

318
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:56,283
[melancholic music continues]

319
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:07,920
So, are we just going to stare
at each other here?

320
00:18:08,003 --> 00:18:11,507
Ah, I know this…

321
00:18:12,091 --> 00:18:13,133
this child.

322
00:18:13,217 --> 00:18:16,053
She’s the beggar I was helping.

323
00:18:16,136 --> 00:18:18,305
I didn’t know she followed me here.

324
00:18:18,388 --> 00:18:20,224
You, you’re really so stubborn.

325
00:18:20,307 --> 00:18:23,560
[inquisitive music playing]

326
00:18:23,644 --> 00:18:25,938
Uh, yes, sorry.

327
00:18:26,021 --> 00:18:31,235
I got hungry, so I looked for Master--

328
00:18:31,318 --> 00:18:32,945
I mean Big Brother.

329
00:18:33,529 --> 00:18:38,075
Maybe you have food there, madam?

330
00:18:38,826 --> 00:18:42,329
Stop it. I’m not a charity organization.

331
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:44,414
Yes, I know that. This girl,

332
00:18:44,498 --> 00:18:45,749
she’s really so stubborn.
I’m really sorry.

333
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:46,792
Come on. Let’s go, let’s go.

334
00:18:47,626 --> 00:18:49,670
[Atoy] Come, come, follow me here.

335
00:18:52,631 --> 00:18:57,177
You people, tighten up security.

336
00:18:57,970 --> 00:19:00,889
A child? Slipped past you?

337
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:02,724
Really?

338
00:19:03,517 --> 00:19:04,768
Sorry, ma’am.

339
00:19:06,478 --> 00:19:09,022
[tense music playing]

340
00:19:09,106 --> 00:19:11,441
Good thing you were there, Master.

341
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:14,027
Otherwise, I’d probably be dead.

342
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:15,904
You really are so stubborn, aren’t you?

343
00:19:17,364 --> 00:19:19,074
Didn’t I warn you?

344
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:20,242
What did you do?

345
00:19:20,826 --> 00:19:22,369
You ran away from Karla!

346
00:19:22,452 --> 00:19:23,370
Unbelievable!

347
00:19:23,453 --> 00:19:25,706
What do you think this is, just a game?

348
00:19:26,331 --> 00:19:28,125
You almost got yourself hurt!

349
00:19:28,208 --> 00:19:30,460
And because of that,
my plans almost got ruined.

350
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:32,337
So, it’s my fault?

351
00:19:33,088 --> 00:19:35,340
I asked you about Big Sister Ame,

352
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:37,551
but you didn’t seem to care.

353
00:19:38,927 --> 00:19:42,556
Then earlier, you said you’d rather
prioritize the rooster!

354
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:45,601
Should Sister Ame just wait?

355
00:19:45,684 --> 00:19:47,728
That’s why I said I’ll do it myself.

356
00:19:47,811 --> 00:19:48,729
[Atoy] Wow! [scoffs]

357
00:19:48,812 --> 00:19:50,564
What are you thinking?

358
00:19:50,647 --> 00:19:52,399
You think it’s that easy?

359
00:19:52,482 --> 00:19:53,525
Hey!

360
00:19:53,609 --> 00:19:57,654
You don’t know what kind of people
took your Big Sister Ame!

361
00:19:58,822 --> 00:20:00,991
What you’re doing is dangerous.
Don’t you get it?

362
00:20:01,074 --> 00:20:03,785
I told you I’d find a way, right?!

363
00:20:03,869 --> 00:20:07,539
Just because I don’t say anything
doesn’t mean I’m not doing anything.

364
00:20:08,123 --> 00:20:10,125
I told you I’ll do it.

365
00:20:10,209 --> 00:20:12,127
Don’t you trust me?

366
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:13,253
Well!

367
00:20:13,337 --> 00:20:14,504
Who knows?

368
00:20:14,588 --> 00:20:16,256
Maybe you’re just lying.

369
00:20:16,340 --> 00:20:17,341
Psst! Hey!

370
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:20,427
I’m not that kind of person.

371
00:20:21,511 --> 00:20:25,974
[gentle music playing]

372
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:27,392
All right.

373
00:20:28,018 --> 00:20:30,020
I need to go back there.
I need to finish this!

374
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:33,023
So, I can reunite you with your sister…

375
00:20:33,774 --> 00:20:36,026
and she can handle your stubbornness.

376
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:37,945
Yes, that’s better!

377
00:20:38,737 --> 00:20:42,741
This wouldn’t have happened
if you were easier to talk to!

378
00:20:43,325 --> 00:20:45,035
But don’t worry.

379
00:20:45,619 --> 00:20:50,707
Just bring back Big Sister Ame,
and you won’t see us again.

380
00:20:50,791 --> 00:20:51,625
[Atoy] Really?

381
00:20:52,459 --> 00:20:55,254
Yes! I’ll bring back Big Sister Ame!

382
00:20:55,337 --> 00:21:00,133
[gentle music continues]

383
00:21:07,808 --> 00:21:11,436
[indistinct chatter]

384
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:12,980
That one’s probably not a girl.

385
00:21:13,730 --> 00:21:14,856
[in English] Hey, bro, don’t worry.

386
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:16,191
[in English] We’ll get them next time.

387
00:21:16,275 --> 00:21:17,567
And we didn’t even practice.

388
00:21:17,651 --> 00:21:18,485
- Hey!
- Wow!

389
00:21:18,568 --> 00:21:20,279
Do you know why we won?
We got a good cheerleader.

390
00:21:20,362 --> 00:21:22,906
- [girl] Of course.
- [boy] That’s right. She’s amazing.

391
00:21:24,157 --> 00:21:27,995
[feel-good dreamy music playing]

392
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:34,710
Yo, PJ.

393
00:21:34,793 --> 00:21:35,711
[in English] Yes?

394
00:21:36,837 --> 00:21:38,130
[dreamy music continues]

395
00:21:38,213 --> 00:21:39,548
- [in English] Why?
- [in English] Who is that girl?

396
00:21:39,631 --> 00:21:40,674
[in English] Is she from here?

397
00:21:41,675 --> 00:21:43,427
It’s my first time seeing her here.

398
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:45,012
You like her, bro?

399
00:21:48,724 --> 00:21:49,766
[Cita] Karla!

400
00:21:49,850 --> 00:21:53,395
I’ve been calling you.
You were not answering your cell phone.

401
00:21:53,478 --> 00:21:54,855
What’s the point of having a cell phone?

402
00:21:54,938 --> 00:21:57,524
Sorry, Ma. We were playing basketball.

403
00:21:57,607 --> 00:21:59,401
Look. I raised more money!

404
00:21:59,901 --> 00:22:01,403
Why, what’s that for, Ma?

405
00:22:03,238 --> 00:22:05,741
Miss Cita said you’re being sent home.

406
00:22:06,783 --> 00:22:08,243
Where’s Ibyang anyway?

407
00:22:10,829 --> 00:22:11,872
[mischievous music playing]

408
00:22:11,955 --> 00:22:13,582
Shucks! Where did she go?

409
00:22:13,665 --> 00:22:16,501
She told me earlier
she was going to buy snacks.

410
00:22:16,585 --> 00:22:17,627
What?!

411
00:22:17,711 --> 00:22:19,546
When did she leave?

412
00:22:19,629 --> 00:22:21,673
Earlier, before the game started.

413
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:24,634
Oh?
We’ve been playing for three hours, Karla.

414
00:22:24,718 --> 00:22:25,594
[Karla] What?!

415
00:22:26,845 --> 00:22:30,057
- I’ll look for her, Ma, I promise.
- Oh my gosh!

416
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:32,434
[phone ringing]

417
00:22:32,517 --> 00:22:34,936
Shucks! It’s Big Brother Atoy.

418
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:36,980
INCOMING CALL
BROTHER ATOY

419
00:22:39,775 --> 00:22:42,778
- Hello, brother.
- [Atoy] <i>Oh, Karla?</i>

420
00:22:42,861 --> 00:22:45,030
Guess where Ibyang is now.

421
00:22:45,113 --> 00:22:46,615
Brother, I’m sorry!

422
00:22:48,575 --> 00:22:51,119
You’re unbelievable!
I told you to watch her.

423
00:22:51,203 --> 00:22:53,914
I rarely give you orders,
and she still managed to escape from you.

424
00:22:53,997 --> 00:22:56,124
Brother, I admit, it’s my fault.

425
00:22:56,208 --> 00:22:58,251
We got carried away playing basketball.

426
00:22:58,335 --> 00:23:00,378
I didn’t notice she bolted.

427
00:23:01,171 --> 00:23:02,255
Well then, pick her up here.

428
00:23:02,339 --> 00:23:04,883
She’s at the eatery near Endless Nights.

429
00:23:04,966 --> 00:23:06,635
Okay, sorry, brother.

430
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:11,807
[somber music playing]

431
00:23:17,646 --> 00:23:18,563
What?

432
00:23:18,647 --> 00:23:20,107
Ibyang is with Big Brother Atoy.
I’ll just get her.

433
00:23:20,190 --> 00:23:21,733
- [Cita sighs] Thank goodness!
- [boy] Hey.

434
00:23:21,817 --> 00:23:23,068
Tonet, you take care of the shop.

435
00:23:23,151 --> 00:23:25,278
- I’ll go get the girl. Come on.
- [Tonet mumbles]

436
00:23:25,362 --> 00:23:26,613
Come on!

437
00:23:26,696 --> 00:23:29,366
[dreamy music playing]

438
00:23:35,038 --> 00:23:36,289
Excuse me, brother.

439
00:23:36,873 --> 00:23:38,750
So grumpy.

440
00:23:39,251 --> 00:23:42,587
Big Brother Atoy! Your makeup looks good.

441
00:23:42,671 --> 00:23:44,131
Your Big Brother has work today.

442
00:23:44,214 --> 00:23:45,924
[Cita] We’ll take care of Ibyang.

443
00:23:48,176 --> 00:23:49,010
Oh?

444
00:23:49,094 --> 00:23:50,971
Miss Cita. Big Sister Karla?

445
00:23:52,013 --> 00:23:53,515
What are you doing here?

446
00:23:53,598 --> 00:23:55,308
Why are you here?!

447
00:23:55,392 --> 00:23:58,186
You were just at the court earlier!
You’ll get me in trouble!

448
00:23:58,770 --> 00:24:00,313
Why did you come here?

449
00:24:01,773 --> 00:24:03,316
Sorry, sister.

450
00:24:03,900 --> 00:24:06,820
I just went to see Big Sister Ame,

451
00:24:06,903 --> 00:24:09,406
but Master Grumpy sent me away.

452
00:24:10,031 --> 00:24:10,866
Well, of course he’s angry.

453
00:24:12,325 --> 00:24:13,785
Because you’re stubborn!

454
00:24:13,869 --> 00:24:16,913
I was just worried about Big Sister Ame.

455
00:24:17,747 --> 00:24:19,666
She’s the only family I have.

456
00:24:21,209 --> 00:24:23,378
She’s been so kind to me.

457
00:24:23,461 --> 00:24:25,839
Kind? Teaching you to be a snatcher?

458
00:24:26,423 --> 00:24:27,966
You don’t know her!

459
00:24:29,801 --> 00:24:32,387
Everyone else left me.

460
00:24:33,263 --> 00:24:36,057
Only Big Sister Ame came back for me.

461
00:24:38,393 --> 00:24:43,231
Big Sister Ame saved me
when the orphanage burned down!

462
00:24:43,815 --> 00:24:44,858
[Ibyang coughs]

463
00:24:44,941 --> 00:24:46,860
- [glass shatters in distance]
- [Ibyang crying]

464
00:24:48,028 --> 00:24:51,239
Help me! I’m still here!

465
00:24:52,199 --> 00:24:53,408
Help!

466
00:24:53,909 --> 00:24:55,368
- [clattering]
- [gasping in fear]

467
00:24:55,452 --> 00:24:56,953
- [crying]
- [rumbling]

468
00:24:57,746 --> 00:24:58,705
Help!

469
00:24:58,788 --> 00:25:00,207
[intense music playing]

470
00:25:01,499 --> 00:25:02,375
[Ibynag coughs]

471
00:25:03,376 --> 00:25:05,295
[glasses shattering in distance]

472
00:25:05,378 --> 00:25:06,713
Help!

473
00:25:06,796 --> 00:25:07,839
- [explosion]
- [screams]

474
00:25:07,923 --> 00:25:10,884
[crying]

475
00:25:10,967 --> 00:25:12,886
[gasping]

476
00:25:15,180 --> 00:25:16,181
- [clatters]
- [coughs]

477
00:25:16,264 --> 00:25:21,019
- [breathing heavily]
- [glass shatters]

478
00:25:22,229 --> 00:25:25,357
[screams]

479
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:26,775
[crying]

480
00:25:26,858 --> 00:25:28,902
[coughing]

481
00:25:29,945 --> 00:25:30,904
Help!

482
00:25:31,905 --> 00:25:33,323
[coughing]

483
00:25:33,406 --> 00:25:40,330
[sobbing]

484
00:25:40,413 --> 00:25:43,750
[intense music continues]

485
00:25:51,049 --> 00:25:53,802
[melancholic music playing]

486
00:26:22,497 --> 00:26:23,665
[sirens wailing]

487
00:26:27,043 --> 00:26:28,378
[woman] The children no longer
have a place to live.

488
00:26:29,045 --> 00:26:31,256
[man] And we’re about
to lose our jobs too.

489
00:26:32,507 --> 00:26:34,050
What will happen to them?

490
00:26:34,134 --> 00:26:38,096
I’m sure they’ll just be crammed
into another orphanage.

491
00:26:39,431 --> 00:26:44,686
- [somber music playing]
- [sirens blaring]

492
00:27:12,797 --> 00:27:14,591
- For sure, they’ll be burning money later.
- [sinister music playing]

493
00:27:14,674 --> 00:27:18,636
So, expect our DOM customers to flock in.

494
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:21,931
That’s a win. Those guests tip big.

495
00:27:22,015 --> 00:27:23,725
Especially those betting on the fight.

496
00:27:23,808 --> 00:27:24,684
What kind of fight?

497
00:27:25,268 --> 00:27:26,227
[Atoy] <i>Boxing?</i>

498
00:27:26,311 --> 00:27:27,645
[janitor] <i>Something like that.</i>

499
00:27:27,729 --> 00:27:30,482
<i>But the fighters are dwarfs. It’s brutal.</i>

500
00:27:30,982 --> 00:27:33,109
I’m here at Endless. Come over!

501
00:27:33,193 --> 00:27:34,652
Okay, Boss. I’ll follow you there.

502
00:27:34,736 --> 00:27:36,154
[Mongki] <i>I just need to collect something.</i>

503
00:27:36,237 --> 00:27:37,364
Who’s your enemy?

504
00:27:37,447 --> 00:27:38,365
[Bunda] Well, it’s this…

505
00:27:38,448 --> 00:27:39,282
- [squealing]
- [people screaming]

506
00:27:39,366 --> 00:27:41,826
[screaming]

507
00:27:41,910 --> 00:27:43,453
What? Huh?!

508
00:27:43,536 --> 00:27:45,455
Who else is brave here? What?

509
00:27:45,538 --> 00:27:47,290
Yes, sir, is there a problem?

510
00:27:47,374 --> 00:27:48,458
Someone took my jacket!

511
00:27:48,541 --> 00:27:50,043
Ah…

512
00:27:50,126 --> 00:27:51,044
UP NEXT

513
00:27:51,127 --> 00:27:52,170
Nice!

514
00:27:52,253 --> 00:27:55,882
[intense music continues]

515
00:27:57,801 --> 00:27:59,636
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
